genresAdvancedInfo.name: prog quebec
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Prog Quebec, also known as progressive rock from Quebec, is a subgenre of progressive rock that originated in the French-speaking province of Quebec, Canada. This genre is characterized by its theatrical, symphonic sound, complex arrangements, and poetic lyrics. Prog Quebec bands often incorporate elements of folk, jazz, and classical music into their sound, and sing in both French and English. Some of the most well-known Prog Quebec bands include Harmonium, Maneige, and Morse Code.
